  "prompt": "Does Cyanogen 13.1 on Moto G3 support VOLTE? If yes, how can I turn on?",
  "response": "CyanogenMod 13.1 is based on Android Marshmallow, and support for VoLTE (Voice over LTE) can vary depending on a few factors, including the specific version you have installed, the carrier you use, and whether the ROM has the necessary configurations.\n\nIf your Moto G3 is running CyanogenMod 13.1 and you want to enable VoLTE, here are some steps you can follow to check and potentially enable it:\n\n### Check Carrier Support\n1. **Ensure Carrier Support**: First, check if your carrier supports VoLTE on the Moto G3. Not all carriers or regions support VoLTE, so verify that your plan and network are compatible.\n\n### Settings in CyanogenMod\n1. **Access Settings**: Go to `Settings` on your device.\n2. **Network & Internet**: Tap on `Network & Internet`, then select `Mobile network`.\n3. **Advanced Options**: Look for options like `Advanced`, and check for `VoLTE` settings. If available, turn on the VoLTE option.\n\n### Additional Configuration\n- **APN Settings**: Sometimes, you might need to correct or update your APN (Access Point Name) settings to ensure that VoLTE functions properly. Contact your carrier for the correct APN settings if necessary.\n\n### Check for Compatibility\n- If you do not see an option for VoLTE within the settings, it might be that CyanogenMod 13.1 does not support it on your device, or that a modification is needed.\n\n### Consider Upgrading\n- If VoLTE is essential for you and your current ROM does not support it, you may consider looking for more up-to-date ROMs or official updates from the manufacturer that support VoLTE.\n\nRemember that using custom ROMs can lead to unexpected behavior, and it's essential to have backups of your data before making any changes.",
